column10: Cyclist traveling westbound on Franconia Road in right (of 3) through lane. Sedan in right lane behind cyclists sounded long blast on car horn (proving that the cyclist, with lights and reflective clothing, was visible even after dark). After following for a few hundred feet, passes cyclist without moving left, into center travel lane, nearly avoiding cyclists, while laying on car horn again.
column21: Obvious to the cyclist that the driver was annoyed that the cyclist was in the travel lane, even though there was sufficient (empty) other travels lanes to provide adequate separate to pass.
